<div id="unit12" class="unit-header" style="border-left-color: var(--accent3);">
  <div class="unit-num" style="color:var(--accent3)">Unit 12</div>
  <h2>Working Capital Decisions</h2>
</div>

<div class="section-band"><span class="mark-pill m5">5 Marks</span><hr></div>

<div class="qa-card">
  <div class="qa-q"><div class="qnum">1</div>Define Working Capital. Distinguish Gross and Net Working Capital.</div>
  <div class="qa-a">
    <span class="key-term">Working Capital</span> is the amount of money needed to cover operating costs and represents the company's short-term financing requirements.<br><br>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Concept</th><th>Definition</th><th>Formula</th></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Gross Working Capital</strong></td><td>Total investment in all current assets</td><td>= Total Current Assets</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Net Working Capital</strong></td><td>Excess of current assets over current liabilities</td><td>= Current Assets − Current Liabilities</td></tr>
    </table>
    <strong>Current Assets include:</strong> Cash, Bank, Debtors, Inventory (RM, WIP, FG), Prepaid Expenses, Short-term Investments<br>
    <strong>Current Liabilities include:</strong> Creditors, Bills Payable, Bank Overdraft, Outstanding Expenses, Taxes payable
  </div>
</div>

<div class="qa-card">
  <div class="qa-q"><div class="qnum">2</div>Explain the Operating Cycle Concept with formula.</div>
  <div class="qa-a">
    <span class="key-term">Operating Cycle</span> = Time taken to convert current assets (excluding cash) back into cash. The longer the cycle, the more working capital is needed.<br><br>
    <div class="diagram">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 560 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100%">
        <defs><marker id="arr2" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="6" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><polygon points="0 0, 8 3, 0 6" fill="#38d9a9"/></marker></defs>
        <circle cx="280" cy="100" r="55" fill="none" stroke="#2e3451" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5,4"/>
        <rect x="230" y="15" width="100" height="34" rx="5" fill="#21263a" stroke="#38d9a9" stroke-width="1.2"/>
        <text x="280" y="37" fill="#38d9a9" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">Raw Material</text>
        <rect x="420" y="70" width="110" height="34" rx="5" fill="#21263a" stroke="#f7c948" stroke-width="1.2"/>
        <text x="475" y="85" fill="#f7c948" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">Work-in-</text>
        <text x="475" y="98" fill="#f7c948" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">Process (WIP)</text>
        <rect x="230" y="155" width="100" height="34" rx="5" fill="#21263a" stroke="#f06595" stroke-width="1.2"/>
        <text x="280" y="177" fill="#f06595" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">Finished Goods</text>
        <rect x="30" y="70" width="100" height="34" rx="5" fill="#21263a" stroke="#4f8ef7" stroke-width="1.2"/>
        <text x="80" y="90" fill="#4f8ef7" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">Cash / Debtors</text>
        <path d="M330 32 Q420 32 430 72" stroke="#38d9a9" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
        <path d="M480 104 Q480 160 332 172" stroke="#f7c948" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
        <path d="M228 172 Q80 172 82 106" stroke="#f06595" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
        <path d="M82 68 Q82 32 228 30" stroke="#4f8ef7" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
        <text x="280" y="96" fill="#8892b0" font-size="9" text-anchor="middle">OPERATING</text>
        <text x="280" y="109" fill="#8892b0" font-size="9" text-anchor="middle">CYCLE</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <strong>Components:</strong>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Period</th></tr>
      <tr><td>RMCP – Raw Material Conversion Period</td><td>Purchase to production issuance</td></tr>
      <tr><td>WIPCP – Work in Progress Conversion Period</td><td>RM issued to finished goods</td></tr>
      <tr><td>FGCP – Finished Goods Conversion Period</td><td>FG transfer to sale</td></tr>
      <tr><td>BDCP – Book Debt Collection Period</td><td>Sale to cash collection</td></tr>
      <tr><td>PDP – Payment Deferral Period</td><td>Credit extended by suppliers</td></tr>
